Job description:

We are seeking a highly skilled and creative Generative AI Developer/Engineer to join our AI Development team. As a Gen AI Engineer, you will play a pivotal role in designing, developing, and deploying generative AI models that produce creative and novel content, including text, images, and more at scale. You will collaborate with cross-functional teams and leverage powerful AI techniques to create innovative solutions that push the boundaries of generative AI.

Key responsibilities:

Continuous Learning:

Research the latest advancements in generative AI, staying up-to-date with powerful techniques and models;
Understand the advantages of each generative AI model on the market, including token limits, cost structure, ease of use, commercial availability, ability to fine tune and data privacy.

Data Preprocessing:

Prepare and preprocess data in the cloud and on distributed systems to train generative models, ensuring data quality and compatibility with the chosen model.

Model Training:

Design and develop generative models based on innovative neural network architectures;
Train and fine-tune/p-tune/prompt-engineer generative models using large and sophisticated datasets;
Experiment with model hyperparameters, embeddings, architectures, and training methodologies to optimize model performance;
Supervise model training and make adjustments to optimize model performance.

Evaluation and Testing:

Develop evaluation metrics and conduct rigorous testing to assess the quality and creativity of generated content;
Implement strategies to prevent and address common generative AI issues, such as mode collapse, bias, guardrails, and hallucinations.

Model Deployment:

Deploy generative models in cloud and on-prem production environments to ensure scalability, efficiency, low latency, and optimized compute costs;
Collaborate with DevOps and engineering teams to integrate models into software applications and systems.

Collaboration:

Work closely with cross-functional teams, including data scientists, software engineers, end users and product managers, to understand project requirements and objectives;
Participate in collaborative brainstorming sessions and contribute creative ideas for potential applications of generative AI.

Required Skills

Bachelor's degree in computer science, math, statistics, engineering, physics, or a related quantitative field (Master's or Ph.D. preferred);
Proven experience in developing generative AI models and projects;
Proficiency in programming languages such as Python and deep learning frameworks such as TensorFlow or PyTorch;
Deep understanding of generative models, deep learning architectures, and neural networks;
Experience with data preprocessing and data wrangling techniques;
Knowledge of model deployment and cloud services (e.g., AWS, Azure, GCP);
Excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to work both independently and as part of a team;
Strong communication and presentation skills;
A passion for exploring the creative possibilities of generative AI.

